{"title": "Pushing to the Front", "description": "Published in 1894, this is the first book by the renowned inspirational author, Dr. Orison Swett Marden. <em>Pushing to the Front</em> is the product of many years of hard work, and marks a turning point in the life of Dr. Marden. He rewrote it following an accidental fire that brought the five-thousand-plus page manuscript to flames. It went on to become the most popular personal-development book of its time, and is a timeless classic in its genre. Filled with stories of success, triumph and the surmounting of difficulties, it is especially well-targeted at the adolescent or young adult. It is a book to inspire the reader towards a noble sense of integrity, a strong moral foundation, and solid, enduring self-discipline to let the reader put each foot forward as the leader they are meant to be. (Summary by Luke Sartor)", "duration": 119897, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "6183", "name": " Orison Swett Marden"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt33/Pushing_to_the_Front_1401.jpg", "copyright_year": "1894", "genres": ["Psychology", "Self-Help", "Modern"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Luke Sartor"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Luke Sartor"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Ruth Golding"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Lucretia B."}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Foreword", "readers": [7942], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/pushingtofront_ls_librivox/pushingtothefront_00_marden_64kb.mp3", "duration": 396}, {"section": 1, "title": "Chapter I: The Man and the Opportunity", "readers": [7942], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/pushingtofront_ls_librivox/pushingtothefront_01_marden_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2463}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapter II: Wanted - a Man", "readers": [7942], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/pushingtofront_ls_librivox/pushingtothefront_02_marden_64kb.mp3", "duration": 906}, {"section": 3, "title":